## Parent Story
#4

## Complexity
medium

## Files
tests/nlp_test.rs

---

## Overview

Create tests for NLP module covering both CI-runnable unit tests and integration tests. CI-runnable tests (75% of tests) mock LLM behavior; integration tests require Ollama.

## Implementation

Create `tests/nlp_test.rs`:

```rust
use sage_dice::nlp::{build_prompt, parse_response, NlpResponse};

// === CI-RUNNABLE TESTS (no Ollama required) ===

#[test]
fn test_build_prompt() {
    let prompt = build_prompt("roll a d20");
    assert!(prompt.contains("dice notation translator"));
    assert!(prompt.contains("roll a d20"));
}

#[test]
fn test_build_prompt_empty_input() {
    let prompt = build_prompt("");
    assert!(prompt.contains("dice notation translator"));
}

#[test]
fn test_parse_response_valid_simple() {
    let response = r#"{"notation": "2d6+3", "explanation": "two dice plus three"}"#;
    let result = parse_response(response).unwrap();
    assert_eq!(result.notation, "2d6+3");
    assert_eq!(result.explanation, "two dice plus three");
}

#[test]
fn test_parse_response_with_surrounding_text() {
    // LLM sometimes adds explanatory text around JSON
    let response = r#"Sure! Here's the result: {"notation": "4d6kh3", "explanation": "roll 4d6 keep highest 3"} Hope that helps!"#;
    let result = parse_response(response).unwrap();
    assert_eq!(result.notation, "4d6kh3");
}

#[test]
fn test_parse_response_with_newlines() {
    // JSON might be multiline
    let response = r#"{
    "notation": "1d20",
    "explanation": "single d20"
}"#;
    let result = parse_response(response).unwrap();
    assert_eq!(result.notation, "1d20");
}

#[test]
fn test_parse_response_no_json() {
    let response = "No JSON here, just text";
    assert!(parse_response(response).is_err());
}

#[test]
fn test_parse_response_empty_object() {
    let response = "{}";
    let result = parse_response(response);
    // Empty object should fail validation (missing fields)
    assert!(result.is_err());
}

#[test]
fn test_parse_response_missing_notation_field() {
    let response = r#"{"explanation": "test"}"#;
    let result = parse_response(response);
    assert!(result.is_err());
}

// === INTEGRATION TESTS (require Ollama running) ===

#[test]
#[ignore = "Requires Ollama running locally at localhost:11434"]
fn test_query_ollama_d20() {
    use sage_dice::nlp::query_ollama;
    let result = query_ollama("roll a d20").unwrap();
    assert!(result.notation.contains("d20") || result.notation.contains("1d20"));
}

#[test]
#[ignore = "Requires Ollama running locally at localhost:11434"]
fn test_query_ollama_fireball() {
    use sage_dice::nlp::query_ollama;
    let result = query_ollama("fireball damage").unwrap();
    assert!(result.notation.contains("8d6"));
}

#[test]
#[ignore = "Requires Ollama running locally at localhost:11434"]
fn test_query_ollama_advantage() {
    use sage_dice::nlp::query_ollama;
    let result = query_ollama("roll with advantage").unwrap();
    // Should recognize advantage as 2d20kh1
    let notation = &result.notation;
    assert!(notation.contains("2d20") || notation.contains("advantage"));
}

#[test]
#[ignore = "Requires Ollama running locally at localhost:11434"]
fn test_translate_with_fallback() {
    use sage_dice::nlp::translate;
    // Direct notation should work even if Ollama is down
    let result = translate("2d6+3");
    assert!(result.is_ok());
    assert_eq!(result.unwrap(), "2d6+3");
}

#[test]
#[ignore = "Requires Ollama running locally at localhost:11434"]
fn test_translate_nlp_fallback() {
    use sage_dice::nlp::translate;
    // Should attempt NLP translation
    let result = translate("roll two six-sided dice");
    assert!(result.is_ok());
    let notation = result.unwrap();
    // Should contain d6 in some form
    assert!(notation.contains("d6") || notation.contains("dice"));
}
```

## Files to Create

- `tests/nlp_test.rs` - New test file

## Dependencies

Requires Story 1 (#2) to be complete for:
- `NlpResponse` type
- `build_prompt()` function
- `parse_response()` function
- `query_ollama()` function (integration tests)
- `translate()` function (integration tests)

## Success Criteria

- All CI-runnable tests pass with `cargo test` (7 unit tests)
- All integration tests marked with `#[ignore]` and run only with `cargo test -- --ignored`
- `test_build_prompt` verifies system prompt is included
- `test_parse_response_valid_simple` verifies valid JSON parses correctly
- `test_parse_response_with_surrounding_text` verifies JSON extraction from surrounding text
- `test_parse_response_no_json` verifies error when no JSON present
- `test_parse_response_missing_notation_field` verifies validation of required fields
- `test_query_ollama_*` tests run only when Ollama is available
- `test_translate_with_fallback` verifies fallback to direct parse
- 75%+ tests are CI-runnable (7 unit tests out of ~10 total)

